The paper deals with neural encoders and recurrent models for question answering, which are topics typically covered in the arXiv sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV). The paper's focus on learning temporal gates for sequence pairs further suggests that it may be more relevant to the first three sub-categories, which are more closely related to natural language processing and deep learning.
